  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date, federal contract obligations total $456B. Obligations are concentrated in a set of states led by Texas, Virginia, and California: Texas accounts for $69.1B, Virginia for $64.2B, and California for $38.6B. Other states in the top ten include Maryland at $22.5B, Arizona at $20.9B, District Of Columbia at $19.2B, Florida at $18.5B, Pennsylvania at $17.8B, Connecticut at $14.5B, and New Mexico at $13.1B. The page reports total award values as full contract values rather than single-year obligations. These figures reflect the aggregate obligation activity recorded in FY2026 to date and show the absolute dollar amounts by state for the top ten jurisdictions.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "Which states lead federal contract obligations in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "Texas leads with $69.1B in obligations, followed by Virginia with $64.2B and California with $38.6B. Maryland, Arizona, and the District Of Columbia each appear in the next group with $22.5B, $20.9B, and $19.2B respectively. Florida and Pennsylvania record $18.5B and $17.8B. Connecticut and New Mexico complete the top ten with $14.5B and $13.1B."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What is the reported total of federal contract obligations for FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The reported total of federal contract obligations for FY2026 to date is $456B. The total award value figures are noted as full contract values, not single-year obligations. The top ten states listed account for a portion of that $456B in identified obligations. The ranking presents the dollar amounts for each top-ten state as listed."
      }
    ]
  },
